OL,7,FMr Sunak insisted the changes `
OL,8,Fincluding benefits being stopped if
OL,9,Fsomeone does not comply with
OL,10,Fconditions set by a work coach and a
OL,11,Fpledge to "tighten" the work
OL,12,Fcapability assessment (WCA) ` are not
OL,13,Fsolely about cutting costs.
OL,15,FOther proposed changes include having
OL,16,Fso-called specialist work and health
OL,17,Fprofessionals charged with
OL,18,Fresponsibility for issuing fit notes
OL,19,Finstead of GPs ` in a bid to end the
OL,20,F"sick note culture".
